<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="31.[264,1324,865,1478]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authority="Tuomikoski, 1966" authorityName="Tuomikoski" authorityYear="1966" box="[264,663,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Stigmatomeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,435,1132,1157]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stigmatomeria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tuomikoski" box="[446,663,1132,1158]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Tuomikoski, R. (1966) Generic taxonomy of the Exechiini (Dipt., Mycetophilidae). Annales entomologici Fennici, 32, 159 - 194." type="journal article" year="1966">
Tuomikoski, 
<number box="[604,663,1132,1158]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is treated here as a genus following 
<bibRefCitation author="Vockeroth" box="[1116,1318,1132,1158]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. (1980) New genera and species of Mycetophilidae (Diptera) from the Holarctic region, with notes on other species. Canadian Entomologist, 112, 529 - 544." type="journal article" year="1980">
Vockeroth (
<number box="[1255,1318,1132,1158]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1980.1981">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vockeroth" box="[264,324,1172,1198]" pageId="31" pageNumber="35" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. (1981) 14. Mycetophilidae. Vol. 1. In: McAlpine, J. F. et al. (Eds) Manual of Nearctic Diptera. vi + 674 pp. Canada Department of Agriculture, Research Branch, Canada Department of Agriculture, Monograph No. 27, Ottawa, pp. 223 - 246." type="book chapter" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation box="[388,587,1172,1198]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Soli, G. E. E., Vockeroth, J. R. &amp; Matile, L. (2000) Chapter A 4: Families of Sciaroidea. In: Papp, L. &amp; Darvas, B. (Eds) Contributions to a manual of Palaearctic Diptera. Appendix. Budapest: Science Herald, pp. 49 - 92." type="book chapter">
Söli et al. (
<number box="[513,578,1172,1198]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Although this specimen lacks abdomen the generic characters, including vertical blackish marks on the coxae and distinctly swollen flagellars, clearly place it in 
<taxonomicName box="[393,565,1252,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Stigmatomeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,565,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stigmatomeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The determination seems rather safe as the two species names associated to this genus most likely refers only to 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1029,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Mycetophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">
<emphasis box="[856,1029,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. crassicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Soli" box="[1093,1273,1292,1318]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Soli, G. E. E., Vockeroth, J. R. &amp; Matile, L. (2000) Chapter A 4: Families of Sciaroidea. In: Papp, L. &amp; Darvas, B. (Eds) Contributions to a manual of Palaearctic Diptera. Appendix. Budapest: Science Herald, pp. 49 - 92." type="book chapter" year="2000">
Söli et al. 
<number box="[1214,1273,1292,1318]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zaitzev" box="[264,421,1332,1358]" pageId="31" pageNumber="35" refString="Zaitzev, A. I. (2003) Fungus gnats (Diptera, Sciaroidea) of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part II. An international Journal of Dipterological Research, 14, 77 - 386." type="journal article" year="2003">
Zaitzev 
<number box="[358,421,1332,1358]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and since 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[557,744,1332,1358]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1924) Notes on the types of Mycetophilidae (Diptera) described by Staeger and Zetterstedt. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 45, 160 - 168." type="journal article" year="1924">
Edwards (
<number box="[675,736,1332,1358]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who studied the apparently undamaged 
<typeStatus box="[1215,1266,1332,1358]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[388,539,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Mycetophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicoxa">
<emphasis box="[388,539,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">M. spinicoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[607,780,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Mycetophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">
<emphasis box="[607,780,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. crassicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[850,900,1372,1398]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zetterstedt, 1855" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Cordyla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canescens">
<emphasis box="[1044,1266,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cordyla canescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zetterstedt" pageId="31" pageNumber="35" refString="Zetterstedt, J. W. (1855) Diptera scandinaviae disposita et descripta. Lundae 12, xx + 4547 - 4942." type="journal article" year="1855">
Zetterstedt, 
<number box="[366,425,1412,1438]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1855.0">1855</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was unfortunately not located in any of the collections, but the species was synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[464,652,1452,1478]" pageId="31" pageNumber="34" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1924) Notes on the types of Mycetophilidae (Diptera) described by Staeger and Zetterstedt. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 45, 160 - 168." type="journal article" year="1924">
Edwards (
<number box="[583,644,1452,1478]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on a female.
</paragraph>
